personally, i don&#39;t like negative labels in general (including NoSQL).

however, if you wanted to go that route, i&#39;d be more inclined to use NoREST
since that seems to be the point here.

keeping in mind that REST is not an HTTP thing, REST over HTTP is just as
valid a phrase - possibly more accurate.  in cases where i&#39;m in an audience
that my have inaccurate assumptions the nature of REST, i usually use
&quot;REST/HTTP&quot; or &quot;HTTP using REST&quot; or &quot;RESTful HTTP.&quot;

there was some talk of this on the #REST IRC channel, too.
nothing definitive came up there, IIRC.

